Justice Ayokunle Faji of the Federal High Court has convicted and sentenced a drug baron, Chimezie Aniede to six years imprisonment for attempting to export 7.1 Kilograms of a banned substance, Methamphetamine, to Madrid, Spain’s capital. Justice Faji jailed Aniede after he pleaded guilty to a one-count charge of unlawful exportation of the said banned substance. An NDLEA prosecutor, Abu Ibrahim had told the court that the convict was arrested with the banned substance on March 28, 2021, at the Gate ‘C’ of the Departure Hall of the Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Ikeja-Lagos, during the outward clearance of passengers on onboard Royal Air, Maroc, flight from Lagos to Madrid, Spain via Casablanca, Morocco. Ibrahim had maintained that the offence was contrary to and punishable under Section 11(b) of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency Act, Cap. N30, Laws of the Federation Of Nigeria, 2004, The convict had initially pleaded not guilty to the charge when he was first arraigned before the court sometime in 2021. However, at the resumed hearing of the matter on March 31, 2022, the convict, through his lawyer Evans Ezeoke, told the judge that he wanted to change his not guilty plea to guilty. Based on the development, Justice Faji adjourned the case to Friday to enable the prosecutor to review the facts of the case. When the matter was called on Friday, Ibrahim reviewed the facts of the case and tendered some exhibits, which are: the Convict’s confessional statement, his international passport, part of the analysed drug, the bulk of the drug and others who were admitted by the court.